  <section id="about">
    <h3>About Me</h3>
    <p>Hello, I’m <strong>Cristal T. Ellis, LAC</strong>, a Licensed Associate Counselor dedicated to creating a compassionate, nonjudgmental space where clients can feel seen, heard, and supported. I specialize in working with adolescents and adults who are navigating life’s challenges, transitions, and emotional pain.</p>
    <p>My therapeutic approach combines <strong>Cognitive Behavioral Therapy (CBT)</strong>, <strong>Cognitive Processing Therapy (CPT)</strong>, and a <strong>Person-Centered</strong> foundation to meet each client where they are.</p>
  </section>

  <section id="services">
    <h3>Services</h3>
    <div class="service"><strong>Anxiety:</strong> Learn tools to calm your mind and regain control over worry and stress.</div>
    <div class="service"><strong>Depression:</strong> Explore emotions and build healthier coping strategies for brighter days ahead.</div>
    <div class="service"><strong>Grief:</strong> Process loss with compassion and understanding at your own pace.</div>
    <div class="service"><strong>Adjustment Disorders:</strong> Find balance as you adapt to life’s changes and transitions.</div>
